We are a work in progress.

64
00:03:45,431 --> 00:03:47,351
Here's some background on Avalanche Studios.

65
00:03:47,471 --> 00:03:50,852
The company was founded in Stockholm, Sweden 15 years ago.

66
00:03:51,372 --> 00:03:54,133
New York is the only studio outside of Sweden

67
00:03:54,173 --> 00:03:55,553
and opened in 2011.

68
00:03:56,593 --> 00:03:58,733
Avalanche Studios developed Mad Max,

69
00:03:58,793 --> 00:04:00,974
the Just Cause series, the Hunter series,

70
00:04:01,454 --> 00:04:03,214
Rage 2, and Generation Zero.

71
00:04:05,255 --> 00:04:09,455
I was hired for Avalanche Studios three years ago

72
00:04:09,475 --> 00:04:13,156
and I was ecstatic that part of my marching orders

73
00:04:13,196 --> 00:04:14,276
was to do something about DNI.

74
00:04:15,527 --> 00:04:18,130
Like most small to medium video game companies,

75
00:04:19,311 --> 00:04:21,834
it's a struggle to have time, budget, and resources.

76
00:04:22,374 --> 00:04:27,039
DNI is like, aw, that's nice, but nobody really gives time

77
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:30,222
and prioritize it, so it easily gets deprioritized.

78
00:04:31,023 --> 00:04:34,706
I am an HR department of one, of a triple-A studio.

79
00:04:35,107 --> 00:04:37,189
So I, too, have an alibi of being swamped.

80
00:04:38,827 --> 00:04:42,613
So in 2016, I kick-started our D&I initiative

81
00:04:42,673 --> 00:04:45,899
by hiring an external trainer to teach us about D&I.

82
00:04:47,001 --> 00:04:50,326
Unfortunately, the training was not satisfactory.

83
00:04:51,288 --> 00:04:52,290
For the one day event.

84
00:04:53,423 --> 00:04:55,185
We were grouped and asked to complete tasks

85
00:04:55,245 --> 00:04:56,046
around New York City.

86
00:04:56,686 --> 00:04:59,188
Draw on the street, duct tape a tree,

87
00:04:59,849 --> 00:05:01,450
copy a tattoo of a stranger,

88
00:05:02,031 --> 00:05:04,172
eat something we haven't eaten before at Chinatown,

89
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:06,414
invade a store to take a picture,

90
00:05:07,095 --> 00:05:08,696
climb to a rooftop to take a picture.

91
00:05:09,777 --> 00:05:11,098
It was funny when we were doing it,

92
00:05:11,518 --> 00:05:13,520
but the training ended and we realized

93
00:05:15,201 --> 00:05:17,023
we didn't learn anything about DNI.

94
00:05:18,544 --> 00:05:21,326
I felt personally responsible for that failed training.

95
00:05:21,881 --> 00:05:23,422
We did get some of our money back.

96
00:05:23,522 --> 00:05:26,525
The harder part was to gain the trust of employees

97
00:05:26,565 --> 00:05:28,066
that they will not be misled again.

98
00:05:28,947 --> 00:05:31,409
It was fun because it turned out to be a team bonding.

99
00:05:32,089 --> 00:05:33,871
Again, we didn't learn anything about D&I.

100
00:05:36,813 --> 00:05:39,275
This is not to discredit external trainers.

101
00:05:40,296 --> 00:05:42,078
A failed training is actually common

102
00:05:42,278 --> 00:05:44,179
according to the Society of Diversity

103
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:48,823
where I recently got certified to be a diversity practitioner.

104
00:05:49,742 --> 00:05:50,022
Why?

105
00:05:50,042 --> 00:05:57,729
The trainings are the go-to for starting a D&I initiative, and it almost always fails

106
00:05:57,890 --> 00:06:04,216
because it tries to address a huge and complicated topic, which is D&I, in a one-day event.

107
00:06:04,997 --> 00:06:11,943
The more fatal reason why D&I training fails is most companies just stop any initiative

108
00:06:12,123 --> 00:06:13,245
after a failed training.

109
00:06:16,056 --> 00:06:19,439
So the overarching lesson for starting a D&I initiative

110
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:21,701
is slow and consistent steps.

111
00:06:22,162 --> 00:06:25,285
So like this baby, they have milk first

112
00:06:25,345 --> 00:06:26,786
before they move on to solid food.

113
00:06:30,770 --> 00:06:33,672
My first immediate lesson for when I started in 2016

114
00:06:34,233 --> 00:06:37,276
after that D&I failed training

115
00:06:37,596 --> 00:06:40,619
is humility partnered with curiosity.

116
00:06:45,659 --> 00:06:51,284
Humility to accept that this is not a problem that can be solved by one person alone.

117
00:06:52,004 --> 00:06:54,707
And curiosity to start asking questions of what will.

118
00:06:55,427 --> 00:07:03,054
So I did one-on-ones, Google Forum surveys, focus groups to find out what our employees

119
00:07:03,114 --> 00:07:07,097
need, what are the pressing issues, and what are the long-term goals.

120
00:07:08,387 --> 00:07:11,549
The second lesson is commitment to transform by the leadership.

121
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:15,713
This is done through creating and modeling a psychologically safe environment

122
00:07:15,793 --> 00:07:17,794
where people are comfortable to give feedback.

123
00:07:17,814 --> 00:07:21,177
I'm going to say it again, comfortable to give feedback.

124
00:07:21,978 --> 00:07:24,620
We haven't perfected this and this is a never-ending effort.

125
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:27,783
A few steps that we started were we updated the handbook.

126
00:07:28,758 --> 00:07:30,819
communicated the updates to our employees,

127
00:07:31,359 --> 00:07:33,061
called out behavior through one-on-ones

128
00:07:33,081 --> 00:07:34,762
that do not support this initiative,

129
00:07:35,462 --> 00:07:38,124
and leadership also started implementing changes

130
00:07:38,164 --> 00:07:39,425
suggested by employees.

131
00:07:41,646 --> 00:07:43,427
The third lesson is establishing

132
00:07:43,507 --> 00:07:45,028
internal and external partners.

133
00:07:45,709 --> 00:07:48,150
After admitting that the first attempt was a failure,

134
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:50,331
I partnered with the leadership team,

135
00:07:50,772 --> 00:07:53,033
our employees, and specific external groups

136
00:07:53,594 --> 00:07:54,834
to boost our agenda.

137
00:07:55,735 --> 00:07:57,336
I'll give examples in the next slides.

138
00:07:59,285 --> 00:08:03,169
The second overarching lesson is diversity and inclusion

139
00:08:03,229 --> 00:08:04,150
go hand in hand.

140
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:06,051
One cannot work without the other.

141
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:08,754
So you can't just hire a bunch of diverse folks

142
00:08:08,774 --> 00:08:12,358
and say, good luck, because they will not thrive.

143
00:08:12,878 --> 00:08:16,462
So our two goals are foster inclusivity in the company

144
00:08:17,383 --> 00:08:20,025
and increase diversity representation

145
00:08:20,706 --> 00:08:22,268
in the demographics of our employee.

146
00:08:24,887 --> 00:08:26,988
So what are our actions to foster inclusivity?

147
00:08:27,348 --> 00:08:29,388
If I could sum it up in one word,

148
00:08:29,468 --> 00:08:33,029
it's called it's partnership, or creating partnership.

149
00:08:33,609 --> 00:08:35,530
We have three ongoing internal partners.

150
00:08:35,670 --> 00:08:39,651
Number one is the full support of a leadership who listens.

151
00:08:40,391 --> 00:08:43,072
Having D&I considered in our events was a good start.

152
00:08:43,532 --> 00:08:46,773
For example, in representing the company externally,

153
00:08:48,093 --> 00:08:49,853
one small easy step is to make sure

154
00:08:49,913 --> 00:08:52,554
that there's diversity in the representatives we send out.

155
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:57,161
In video game development, the industry is notoriously known for crunch.

156
00:08:58,261 --> 00:09:00,902
You don't like crunch too, right? Or overtime? No?

157
00:09:02,962 --> 00:09:07,083
Admittedly, this is a little easier for us because the company already is established

158
00:09:07,123 --> 00:09:09,544
to be a huge advocate of work-life balance.

159
00:09:10,384 --> 00:09:15,166
We have seven weeks of paid time off and our health, dental, vision insurances

160
00:09:15,266 --> 00:09:20,787
are 100% paid by the company for employee plus dependents, including domestic partners.

161
00:09:22,468 --> 00:09:24,390
Updating policies are also vital.

162
00:09:24,711 --> 00:09:27,314
An easy win for us was changing one of our company paid

163
00:09:27,354 --> 00:09:31,560
holidays, Good Friday holiday, which is a holiday for

164
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:35,385
Christians, to a floating holiday so that others who

165
00:09:35,425 --> 00:09:38,469
don't observe Lent can observe their own holidays.

166
00:09:41,452 --> 00:09:47,015
Establishing our business resource group or BRG is the heart of our D&I team.

167
00:09:47,595 --> 00:09:48,696
How did we start the team?

168
00:09:49,116 --> 00:09:53,338
I scheduled a one-on-one to those who emailed me and spoke to me about the failed training.

169
00:09:54,038 --> 00:09:57,380
I asked them if they were willing to do voluntary work for D&I.

170
00:09:58,180 --> 00:10:00,742
Employees who get it and want to do something about it.

171
00:10:01,242 --> 00:10:04,203
Instructions for a project will remain a priority.

172
00:10:05,257 --> 00:10:08,699
We will meet two to three times a month, and we would plan for activities.

173
00:10:09,099 --> 00:10:11,140
They will not be policing employees.

174
00:10:11,940 --> 00:10:15,182
We started out with eight volunteers and three studio management.

175
00:10:15,342 --> 00:10:19,385
As time went on, there were attrition and addition within the team.

176
00:10:20,245 --> 00:10:23,707
I would like you to be mindful of the word diversity fatigue.

177
00:10:24,568 --> 00:10:29,511
It is a real issue where people get tired and impatient to see immediate changes.

178
00:10:30,559 --> 00:10:33,384
As of this writing, there are six D&I team members.

179
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:36,931
I'm giving a shout out to our remaining OGs.

180
00:10:40,805 --> 00:10:46,408
Third and important partners are every one of us, or employees, who turn out to be our

181
00:10:46,728 --> 00:10:52,151
allies, creating awareness for ourselves and employees about microaggressions, educating

182
00:10:52,171 --> 00:10:57,114
employees of interruptions during meetings and discussions, and implementing zero tolerance

183
00:10:57,174 --> 00:11:02,196
for harassment, plus educating them on how to be an ally, foster an environment ready

184
00:11:02,236 --> 00:11:03,037
for more diversity.

185
00:11:04,138 --> 00:11:09,205
I heard a comment today on if you're a white male and you want to be an ally, what do you do?

186
00:11:10,186 --> 00:11:12,830
Ask that question to the person you want to be an ally to.

187
00:11:15,972 --> 00:11:21,096
In 2017, we started partnering with the following external allies, the academia,

188
00:11:21,216 --> 00:11:24,118
non-profit organizations, and local New York groups.

189
00:11:24,738 --> 00:11:28,420
We've hired incredible talents from our partner universities.

190
00:11:29,161 --> 00:11:32,303
These employees also help out with school outreach.

191
00:11:33,063 --> 00:11:36,286
Since there are not a lot of guides and materials out there to

192
00:11:37,873 --> 00:11:39,333
Help us make D&I work.

193
00:11:39,453 --> 00:11:41,354
Partnering with non-profit organizations

194
00:11:41,414 --> 00:11:43,515
have been extremely helpful to our cause.

195
00:11:44,375 --> 00:11:47,197
Tapping on their specialities are vital

196
00:11:47,357 --> 00:11:49,157
and time plus cost efficient for us.

197
00:11:50,098 --> 00:11:52,279
Lastly, our local New York video game groups.

198
00:11:52,939 --> 00:11:55,560
New York is home to talented indie game developers.

199
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:58,941
Our being at events show our support and oneness.

200
00:11:59,181 --> 00:12:01,922
We provide resources through talks by our developers

201
00:12:02,463 --> 00:12:03,963
and we also share our expertise.

202
00:12:05,703 --> 00:12:09,848
It has been a struggle and a balancing act to find thoughtful activities that make our

203
00:12:09,888 --> 00:12:12,311
D&I initiative sustainable and efficient.

204
00:12:12,971 --> 00:12:17,056
A few of our favorite and successful activities are awareness activities.

205
00:12:17,757 --> 00:12:19,739
These are high impact, educational,

206
00:12:20,708 --> 00:12:21,868
and the cost is minimal.

207
00:12:22,248 --> 00:12:23,228
Here are some examples.

208
00:12:23,968 --> 00:12:26,269
Roundtables are made of a panel.

209
00:12:26,429 --> 00:12:28,509
They are volunteers, depending on the topic,

210
00:12:29,009 --> 00:12:31,070
who have stories to tell, and there's a moderator.

211
00:12:31,610 --> 00:12:33,590
We've had good success with our roundtables,

212
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:35,470
but they require a lot of preparation.

213
00:12:36,251 --> 00:12:38,971
One learning experience for me from a roundtable

214
00:12:39,191 --> 00:12:43,392
is I have an employee who I have difficulty talking to

215
00:12:43,432 --> 00:12:46,092
because at times he has difficulty understanding.

216
00:12:46,572 --> 00:12:48,413
At that roundtable, he shared that

217
00:12:50,101 --> 00:12:56,087
Spanish is his second language, and he felt really bad that his parents didn't speak English,

218
00:12:56,147 --> 00:13:00,751
that he wished that they did so that he won't be in this predicament.

219
00:13:02,173 --> 00:13:05,936
Him having shared that really helped me in terms of communicating with him.

220
00:13:07,338 --> 00:13:08,879
The next one is documentaries.

221
00:13:09,059 --> 00:13:11,521
These are easy and have high impact.

222
00:13:11,961 --> 00:13:14,763
We choose a documentary that's based on a monthly theme.

223
00:13:15,484 --> 00:13:17,325
Newsletters are a collection of research

224
00:13:17,385 --> 00:13:19,727
on a topic that we would like for our employees to know.

225
00:13:20,688 --> 00:13:23,510
Based on feedback, we hired a trainer again,

226
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:26,532
geared to empowering women and the marginalized.

227
00:13:26,872 --> 00:13:29,274
This time it was useful because it was targeted

228
00:13:29,414 --> 00:13:30,375
and it was specific.

229
00:13:32,285 --> 00:13:36,509
More importantly, our conversations are the soul of our D&I initiatives.

230
00:13:36,949 --> 00:13:40,612
For management, making sure all issues and concerns are listened to

231
00:13:40,632 --> 00:13:46,878
and resolved as much as we can. For employees, encouraging difficult conversations,

232
00:13:47,578 --> 00:13:51,121
help foster a good working relationship with their co-workers.

233
00:13:52,580 --> 00:13:55,340
Two key things to maintain an active D&I initiatives

234
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:59,922
are planning a monthly theme as focus for the D&I initiatives.

235
00:14:00,382 --> 00:14:03,522
This helps immensely since the D&I team all

236
00:14:03,562 --> 00:14:05,343
have full-time jobs in the company.

237
00:14:06,163 --> 00:14:08,944
Next is sending a feedback form through Google Form.

238
00:14:09,124 --> 00:14:09,664
That's free.

239
00:14:10,244 --> 00:14:13,025
After every event, to know real time if the activity

240
00:14:13,105 --> 00:14:14,225
was effective or not.

241
00:14:15,305 --> 00:14:17,466
I'm going to share and spend some time talking

